headline: Exclusive-JPMorgan weighs London HQ options as it outgrows Canary Wharf tower, sources say
summary: LONDON (Reuters) -JPMorgan is assessing options for its European headquarters in London as the fast-expanding Wall Street bank outgrows its existing tower in London's Canary Wharf financial district, three sources familiar with the matter told Reuters.  The bank has begun examining options for where to base around 12,000 staff in London, with a decision likely to be made some time after U.S. staff move into their new global headquarters in New York next year, the sources said.
